  "doc_id": "27932",
  "text": "Dendritic cells (DC) are specialized in antigen presentation which plays a key role in the initiation of primary immune responses. Immature DC phagocyte and process antigens and after maturation they stimulate antigen specific T cells. This is the prerequisite for orchestrating the cellular and humoral immune response [CITATION_1] .",
